      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) features the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six powerplant, delivering 320hp through a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. The M96 engine has been proactively addressed with an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal, mitigating common failure points. Utilizing the reinforced Turbo-spec wide-body chassis, this C4S offers superior torsional rigidity and the high-performance 'Big Red' four-piston monobloc Brembo braking system with cross-drilled rotors. The viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system ensures optimal torque distribution, while the suspension geometry remains tight with consistent damping rates. A mechanically honest example for the discerning driver seeking the analog feedback of a wide-body 911.",
